Standard and Poor's Corp said it cut toA-2 from A-1 the commercial paper of Tektronix Inc.    S and P cited the management's plan to repurchase up to 380mln dlrs of common equity. The plan will greatly reduceliquidity and raise debt to total capital by increasingTektronix's sensitivity to industry volatility. Because weakprimary markets have led to slow growth in recent years, astrong balance sheet has been a major support for creditquality, the agency noted.    It added that the firm may improve long-term growth, butincreased competition may inhibit a return to previous levels. Reuter&#3;